output_list.description: The 'distribute' function has an integer overflow in the line 'totalAmount += _amounts[a];', allowing an attacker to set an arbitrary value for an arbitrary user, causing an integer overflow in the 'balances[_to] += _amounts[b];' statement, leading to unauthorized deductions and logical inconsistencies.
Predictable winner selection without secure randomness, enabling DoS attacks.

The 'PayWinner' function has an integer overflow in the line 'balanceOf[_to] += _value;', allowing an attacker to set an arbitrary value for an arbitrary user, causing an integer overflow in the 'balanceOf[msg.sender] -= _value;' statement, leading to unauthorized deductions and logical inconsistencies.
Relies on outdated constructor naming conventions prone to typos.

The 'setSelling' function has an integer overflow in the line 'balanceOf[_to] += _value;', allowing an attacker to set an arbitrary value for an arbitrary user, causing an integer overflow in the 'balanceOf[msg.sender] -= _value;' statement, leading to unauthorized deductions and logical inconsistencies.
